This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it discusses the use of deep learning for mobile devices, which is a common application of computer vision. Additionally, the paper explores the compressibility of representations in MobileNetV2, which is a popular computer vision model. 

The paper is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it discusses the use of deep learning and explores the trade-off between computation cost, communication bandwidth, and model accuracy. 

The Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses the computational requirements of deep learning and explores ways to reduce those requirements. 

Finally, the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category is a possibility as the paper discusses the idea of sharing computational costs between local devices and the cloud, which is a distributed computing problem.
